land]]\n|2018||5||1\n|-\n|2019||4||0\n|-\n!colspan=2|Total||9||1\n|}\n\n===International goals===\n{{updated|match played 17 November 2019. England score listed first, score column indicates score after each Alexander-Arnold goal.}}<ref name=NFT/>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\"\n|+ International goals by date, venue, cap, opponent, score, result and competition\n|-\n!scope=col|No.\n!scope=col|Date\n!scope=col|Venue\n!scope=col|Cap\n!scope=col|Opponent\n!scope=col|Score\n!scope=col|Result\n!scope=col|Competition\n!scope=col class=unsortable|{{abbr|Ref.|Reference}}\n|-\n!scope=row style=text-align:center|1\n|15 November 2018||[[Wembley Stadium]], London, England||align=center|5||{{fb|United States}}||align=center|2\u20130||align=center|3\u20130||[[Exhibition game#Association football|Friendly]]||align=center|<ref name=USA/>\n|}\n\n==Honours==\n[[File:LFC Parade 2019 01.jpg|thumb|Alexander-Arnold (far right) was part of the Liverpool squad which won the [[UEFA Champions League]] trophy in 2019.]]\n'''Liverpool'''\n*[[UEFA Champions League]]: [[2018\u201319 UEFA Champions League|2018\u201319]];<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/48368443 |title=Tottenham Hotspur 0\u20132 Liverpool |first=Phil |last=McNulty |website=BBC Sport |date=1 June 2019 |accessdate=1 June 2019}}</ref> runner-up: [[2017\u201318 UEFA Champions League|2017\u201318]]<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/44258022 |title=Real Madrid 3\u20131 Liverpool |first=Phil |last=McNulty |website=BBC Sport |date=26 May 2018 |accessdate=27 May 2018}}</ref>\n*[[UEFA Super Cup]]: [[2019 UEFA Super Cup|2019]]<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/49332825 |title=Liverpool 2\u20132 Chelsea |first=Gary |last=Rose |website=BBC Sport |date=14 August 2019 |accessdate=15 August 2019}}</ref>\n*[[FIFA Club World Cup]]: [[2019 FIFA Club World Cup|2019]]<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/50869633 |title=Liverpool 1\u20130 Flamengo |first=Harry |last=Poole |website=BBC Sport |date=21 December 2019 |accessdate=21 December 2019}}</ref>\n\n'''England'''\n*[[UEFA Nations League]] third place: [[2018\u201319 UEFA Nations League|2018\u201319]]<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/48191915 |title=Switzerland 0\u20130 England |first=Phil |last=McNulty |website=BBC Sport |date=9 June 2019 |accessdate=12 June 2019}}</ref>\n\n'''Individual'''\n*[[Liverpool Player of the Season Awards|Liverpool Young Player of the Season Award]]: [[2016\u201317 Liverpool F.C. season|2016\u201317]],<ref name=YPOTY/> [[2017\u201318 Liverpool F.C. season|2017\u201318]]<ref name=YPOTY2/>\n*[[PFA Team of the Year]]: [[PFA Team of the Year (2010s)#Premier League 10|2018\u201319 Premier League]]<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/48028713 |title=PFA Team of the Year: Paul Pogba, Raheem Sterling and Sadio Mane included in side |website=BBC Sport |date=25 April 2019 |accessdate=25 April 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Golden Boy (award)|Golden Boy]] runner-up: 2018<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.liverpoolfc.com/news/first-team/330622-trent-alexander-arnold-golden-boy-2018 |title=Alexander-Arnold runner-up in Golden Boy 2018 award |publisher=Liverpool F.C. |last=Williams |first=Sam |date=17 December 2018 |accessdate=30 April 2019}}</ref>\n*UEFA Champions League Squad of the Season: [[2018\u201319 UEFA Champions League#Squad of the season|2018\u201319]]<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/news/newsid=2607890.html |title=UEFA Champions League Squad of the Season |publisher=UEFA |date=2 June 2019 |accessdate=2 June 2019}}</ref>\n*[[UEFA Club Football Awards#Best Defender|UEFA Champions League Defender of the Season]] 3rd place: [[2018\u201319 UEFA Champions League#Defender of the season|2018\u201319]]<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/news/newsid=2617489.html |title=UEFA Champions League Defender of the Season |publisher=UEFA |date=8 August 2019 |accessd