um capacity of 4,901.<ref name=Trusts>{{cite web |title=The Trusts Stadium: Main Arena |url=http://thetrusts-stadium.com/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=12&Itemid=26 |accessdate=2009-02-26 }}{{Dead link|date=November 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> It was also the host venue of the [[2007 Netball World Championships]]. Other matches are also held at the [[North Shore Events Centre]] &ndash; which has a maximum capacity of less than 5,000 &ndash; and at [[Vector Arena]], the largest indoor sports arena in New Zealand, with a capacity of over 12,000.<ref name=nsec>{{cite web |title=North Shore Events Centre: Facility Info |url=http://www.nseventscentre.co.nz/facility_information.htm |accessdate=2009-02-26 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20081014022221/http://www.nseventscentre.co.nz/facility_information.htm |archivedate=October 14, 2008 }}</ref><ref name=vector>{{cite web |title=Vector Arena: Facts & Facilities |url=http://www.vectorarena.co.nz/index.cfm/PageID/5/ViewPage/Facts+Facilities |accessdate=2009-02-26 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090123155900/http://www.vectorarena.co.nz/index.cfm/PageID/5/ViewPage/Facts+Facilities |archivedate=January 23, 2009 }}</ref>\n\n== Competitive record ==\n\n=== ANZ Championship ===\n{|class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size:95%; text-align: center; width: 85%; margin:1em auto;\"\n|-\n! rowspan=2 style=\"background:#eee; width: 10%;\" | Season\n! colspan=4 style=\"background:#eee; width: 27%;\" | Regular season\n! rowspan=2 style=\"background:#eee; width: 30%;\" | Finals \n! rowspan=2 style=\"background:#eee; width: 13%;\" | Head coach\n|-\n! style=\"background:#eee; width:12%;\"| Standings\n! style=\"background:#eee; width:5%;\" | {{Tooltip|W|Wins}}\n! style=\"background:#eee; width:5%;\" | {{Tooltip|D|Draws}}\n! style=\"background:#eee; width:5%;\" | {{Tooltip|L|Losses}}\n|-\n! colspan=7 style=\"background:#{{Netball colours|Northern Mystics|1}