britology/post/channing-tatum-as-expected-is-peoples-sexiest-man-alive-2012/2012/11/14/5a279eb6-2e0d-11e2-89d4-040c9330702a_blog.html |title=Channing Tatum, as expected, is People's Sexiest Man Alive 2012 |author=Jen Chaney |work=The Washington Post|date=November 14, 2012}}</ref>\n| 32\n|-\n| {{dts|2013|11|19}}\n| [[Adam Levine]]<ref name=\"coulton\">{{cite news|last=Jordan|first=Julie|last2=Coulton|first2=Antoinette|title=Adam Levine Is PEOPLE's Sexiest Man Alive|url= https://people.com/music/adam-levine-is-peoples-sexiest-man-alive/|work=People|date=November 19, 2013|accessdate=February 29, 2020}}</ref>\n| 34\n|-\n| {{dts|2014|11|19}}\n| [[Chris Hemsworth]]<ref>{{cite news|last=Jordan|first=Julie|last2=Coulton|first2=Antoinette|title=Chris Hemsworth Is PEOPLE's Sexiest Man Alive|url=https://people.com/celebrity/chris-hemsworth-is-peoples-sexiest-man-alive-2014/|work=People|date=November 19, 2014|accessdate=February 29, 2020}}</ref>\n| 31\n|-\n| {{dts|2015|11|17}}\n| [[David Beckham]]<ref>{{cite news|last=Leonard|first=Elizabeth|title=David Beckham Is PEOPLE's Sexiest Man Alive!|url=https://people.com/celebrity/david-beckham-is-peoples-sexiest-man-alive/|work=People|date=November 17, 2015|accessdate=November 18, 2015}}</ref>\n| 40\n|-\n| {{dts|2016|11|15}}\n|[[Dwayne Johnson]]<ref>{{cite web|last1=Jordan|first1=Julie|title=Dwayne 'The Rock' Johnson Is This Year's Sexiest Man Alive!|url=http://people.com/celebrity/sexiest-man-alive-2016-dwayne-johnson-the-rock/|website=PEOPLE.com}}</ref>\n|44\n|-\n| {{dts|2017|11|14}}\n|[[Blake Shelton]]<ref>{{cite web|title=Blake Shelton Is This Year's Sexiest Man Alive: 'I Can't Wait to Shove This Up Adam's A\u2014!'|url=http://people.com/country/sexiest-man-alive-blake-shelton-2017-cover-reveal/|website=PEOPLE.com|accessdate=November 15, 2017|date=November 15, 2017}}</ref>\n|41\n|-\n|{{dts|2018|11|5}}\n|[[Idris Elba]]<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://people.com/movies/idris-elba-sexiest-man-alive-2018-reveal/ |title=Idris Elba sexiest man alive 2018 reveal}}</ref>\n|46\n|-\n|{{dts|2019|11|13}}\n|[[John Legend]]<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://people.com/music/john-legend-sexiest-man-alive-2019-reveal/ |title=John Legend Is PEOPLE's Sexiest Man Alive 2019: 'I'm Excited but a Little Scared at the Same Time'}}</ref>\n|40\n|-\n|}\n\n===Sexiest Woman Alive===\n{{See also|Esquire (magazine)#Sexiest Woman Alive|l1=Sexiest Woman Alive (Esquire magazine)}}\nIn December 2014, ''People'' selected its first and only Sexiest Woman Alive.<ref name=NYDNUpton>{{cite web|url=http://www.nydailynews.com/entertainment/gossip/kate-upton-wins-sexiest-woman-article-1.2050992 |title=Kate Upton wins 'Sexiest Woman' |work=Daily News |location=New York |date=December 19, 2014 |accessdate=February 8, 2015}}</ref> No later ''People'' Sexiest Women of the Year were announced.\n[[Cindy Crawford]] alongside [[Richard Gere]] were declared \"Sexiest Couple of the Year\" on October 19, 1993, as a departure from the magazine's annual \"Sexiest Man of the Year\" award.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Choice\n! Age\n|-\n| {{dts|2014|12|25}}\n| [[Kate Upton]]<ref name=NYDNUpton />\n| 22\n|-\n|}\n\n===Most Intriguing People of the Year===\n\nAt the end of each year ''People'' magazine famously selects 25 news-making individuals or couples who have received a lot of media attention over the past 12 months and showcases them in a special year-end issue, the '25 Most Intriguing People of the Year'. This series of full-page features and half-page featurettes includes world leaders and political activists, famous actors and entertainers, elite athletes, prominent business people, accomplished scientists and occasionally members of the public whose stories have made an unusual impact in news or tabloid media.<ref>For example, for the \"Most Intriguing People of 2010\" ''People'' named the following:\n# [[Sandra Bullock]]\n# President [[Barack Obama]] and [[Michelle Obama]]\n# [[Brad Pitt]] and [[Angelina Jolie]]\n# [[Michael Douglas]]\n# [[Elizabeth Smart (activist)|Elizabeth Smart]]\n# [[Prince William, Duke of Cambridge|Prince William]] and [[Catherine, Duchess of Cambridge|Catherine Middleton]]\n# [[Elin Nordegren]]\n# [[Natalie Portman]]\n# [[Nicki Minaj]]\n# [[Sarah Palin]]\n# [[LeBron James]]\n# [[Bret Michaels]]\n# [[Julian Assange]]\n# [[2010 Copiap\u00f3 mining accident#Key members of the trapped group|The Chilean Miners]]\n# [[Ricky Martin]]\n# [[Kim Kardashian]]\n# [[Mark Zuckerberg]]\n# [[Heidi Montag]]\n# [[Jake Gyllenhaal]] and [[Taylor Swift]]\n# [[Ryan Reynolds]]\n# [[Will Smith]]'s kids ([[Jaden Smith|Jaden]] and [[Willow Smith|Willow]])\n# [[Christina Aguilera]]\n# [[Ali Fedotowsky]] and Roberto Martinez\n# [[James Franco]]\n# [[Conan O'Brien]]</ref>\n\n===100 Most Beautiful People===\n''People''{{'}}s 100 Most Beautiful People is an annual list of 100 people judged to be the most beautiful individuals in the world. Until 2006, it was the 50 Most Beautiful People.\n \n[[Julia Roberts]] holds the record for most times named, with five.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://people.com/movies/julia-roberts-worlds-most-beautiful-woman-2017/|title=Julia Roberts Is PEOPLE's 2017 World's Most Beautiful Woman!|first1=Jess|last1=Cable|first2=Lindsay|last2=Kimble|date=April 19, 2017|accessdate=April 19, 2017|archivedate=April 20, 2017|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170420034436/http://people.com/movies/julia-roberts-worlds-most-beautiful-woman-2017/|url-status=live|quote=The stunning star is, for a record fifth time, the Most Beautiful Woman in the World...}}</ref>  [[Michelle Pfeiffer]] and [[Jennifer Aniston]] have appeared twice.\n\n====Number Ones of Most Beautiful People====\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n! Year \n! Name  \n! Age\n|-\n| {{dts|1990|06|01}}\n|[[Michelle Pfeiffer]] (1)\n| 32\n|-\n|{{dts|1991|06|07}}\n|[[Julia Roberts]] (1)\n| 23\n|- \n|{{dts|1992|05|04}}\n|[[Jodie Foster]] \n| 28\n|- \n|{{dts|1993|05|03}}\n|[[Cindy Crawford]] \n| 27\n|- \n|{{dts|1994|05|08}}\n|[[Meg Ryan]] \n| 32\n|- \n|{{dts|1995|05|08}}\n|[[Courteney Cox]] \n| 30\n|- \n|{{dts|1996|05|08}}\n|[[Mel Gibson]]\n| 40\n|- \n|{{dts|1997|05|12}}\n|[[Tom Cruise]]\n| 34\n|- \n|{{dts|1998|05|12}}\n|[[Leonardo DiCaprio]] \n| 23\n|- \n|{{dts|1999|05|14}}\n|[[Michelle Pfeiffer]] (2)\n| 41\n|- \n|{{dts|2000|05|08}}\n|[[Julia Roberts]] (2)\n| 32\n|- \n|{{dts|2001|05|14}}\n|[[Catherine Zeta-Jones]]\n| 31\n|- \n|{{dts|2002|05|13}}\n|[[Nicole Kidman]]\n| 34\n|- \n|{{dts|2003|05|12}}\n|[[Halle Berry]]\n| 36\n|- \n|{{dts|2004|05|30}}\n|[[Jennifer Aniston]] (1)\n| 35\n|- \n|{{dts|2005|05|08}}\n|[[Julia Roberts]] (3)\n| 37\n|- \n|{{dts|2006|04|28}}\n|[[Angelina Jolie]]\n| 30\n|- \n|{{dts|2007|04|27}}\n|[[Drew Barrymore]]\n| 32\n|- \n|{{dts|2008|05|02}}\n|[[Kate Hudson]]\n| 29\n|- \n|{{dts|2009|05|11}}\n|[[Christina Applegate]]\n| 37\n|- \n|{{dts|2010|04|30}}\n|[[Julia Roberts]] (4)\n| 42\n|- \n|{{dts|2011|04|15}}\n|[[Jennifer Lopez]]\n| 41\n|- \n|{{dts|2012|04|27}}\n|[[Beyonc\u00e9|Beyonc\u00e9 Knowles]]\n| 30\n|- \n|{{dts|2013|04|26}}\n|[[Gwyneth Paltrow]]\n| 40\n|-\n|{{dts|2014|05|05}}\n|[[Lupita Nyong'o]]\n| 31\n|-\n|{{dts|2015|04|24}}\n|[[Sandra Bullock]]\n| 50\n|-\n|{{dts|2016|04|20}}\n|[[Jennifer Aniston]] (2)\n| 47\n|-\n|{{dts|2017|04|19}}\n|[[Julia Roberts]] (5)\n| 49\n|-\n|{{dts|2018|04|18}}\n|[[Pink (singer)|Pink]]\n| 38\n|-\n|{{dts|2019|04|24}}\n|[[Jennifer Garner]]\n|47\n|}\n\n==Notes==\n{{cnote|a|The ratio, according to ''Variety'', is 53% to 47%.}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{Official website|mobile=https://m.people.com}}\n\n{{Meredith Corporation}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:People (Magazine)}}\n[[Category:People (magazine)| ]]\n[[Category:Meredith Corporation magazines]]\n[[Category:American weekly magazines]]\n[[Category:American celebrity magazines]]\n[[Category:Magazines established in 1974]]\n", "name_user": "Jacob251299", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "(list)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/People_(magazine)"}
{"title_page": "Bladee", "text_new": "{{Infobox musical artist\n| name             = Bladee\n| background       = solo_singer\n| image            = File:Bladee in Toronto, Canada 2016.jpg\n| caption          = Bladee performing in 2016\n| birth_name       = Benjamin Reichwald\n| alias            = Ken Burns (Sm\u00f6g Boys)\n| birth_date       = {{birth date and age|1994|4|9|df=y}}\n| birth_place      = [[Stockholm, Sweden]]\n| genre            = [[cloud rap]], [[emo rap]], [[experimental pop]]\n| occupation       = [[Rapper]], [[Singing|singer]], [[Fashion designer]], [[Graphic designer]]\n| instrument       = [[Vocals]], [[Digital Audio Workstation]], [[pitch-correction software]]\n| years_active     = 2008; 2011; 2012\u2013present\n| label            = {{hlist|[[YEAR0001]]|[[AWAL]]}}\n| associated_acts  = {{hlist|[[Yung Lean]]|[[Thaiboy Digital]]|[[ECCO2K]]|Whitearmor|Yung Sherman|Gud|Adamn Killa|Cartier'GOD|Black Kray}}\n}}\n'''Benjamin Thage Dag Reichwald'''<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://genius.com/artists/Bladee|title=Bladee|last=|first=|date=|website=Genius|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Borelli-Persson |first1=Laird |title=Is There Anything He Can't Do? Meet Stockholm's Stylish Multi-Hyphenate Zak Arogundade |url=https://www.vogue.com/article/musicians-zak-arogundade |website=[[Vogue (magazine)|Vogue]] |publisher=Cond\u00e9 Nast |accessdate=7 July 2018}}</ref> (born 9 April 1994<ref>{{cite tweet |user=BladeeCity |number=718871748674850816 |date=9 Apr 2016 |title=Thanks everyone that wished me happy birthday}}</ref>), known professionally as '''Bladee''' (pronounced either \"blade\" or \"blade-e\"),<ref>\"Nardwuar vs. Yung Lean\", Youtube video, 12:36, posted by \"[[Nardwuar the Human Serviette|NardwuarServiette]]\", July 23, 2014, https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=723ywF5faV4.</ref> is a Swedish rapper, singer, songwriter, record-producer, fashion designer and member of the musical group [[Drain Gang]].<ref name=Darville2018>{{cite web |last1=Darville |first1=Jordan |title=Listen to Bladee's new album Red Light |url=https://www.thefader.com/2018/05/11/bladee-album-red-light-stream |website=[[The Fader]] |publisher=Andy Cohn |accessdate=7 July 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"Red Light album review\">\"Bladee - Red Light ALBUM REVIEW\", Youtube video, 5:21, posted by \"[[Anthony Fantano|theneedledrop]]\", June 21, 2018, https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=FJwmTnjDkrI.</ref><ref name=\"debut Decay\">{{cite web |last1=Wang |first1=Steffanee |title=Bladee debuts \"Decay,\" our first taste of new album Red Light |url=https://www.thefader.com/2018/05/02/bladee-decay-video-red-light-album |website=[[The Fader]] |publisher=Andy Cohn |accessdate=19 July 2018}}</ref> \n\nHe released his debut album ''[[Eversince (Bladee album)|Eversince]]'' in 2016, and his second album ''[[Red Light (Bladee album)|Red Light]]'' in 2018\u2014both through Stockholm record label [[YEAR0001]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=Jenkins |first1=Craig |title=Stream Yung Lean Associate Bladee's Chilly, Gorgeous Debut Album 'Eversince' |url=https://noisey.vice.com/en_us/article/6e43we/stream-yung-lean-associate-yung-bladees-chilly-gorgeous-debut-album-eversince |website=[[Noisey]] |publisher=[[Vice Media]] |accessdate=7 July 2018}}</ref><ref name=Darville2018 /><ref>YEAR0001. Accessed July 19, 2018. http://www.year0001.com/.</ref> In addition to his music, Reichwald creates visual art, which frequently appears as cover art for his releases.<ref>Sami Baha. \"Bladee - Cover Up (Prod. Sami Baha)\". Soundcloud audio, 2:38, June 27, 2018. https://soundcloud.com/samibaha/bladee-cover-up-prod-sami-baha.</ref><ref>Bala Club. \"Woesum - Sapphire\". Soundcloud audio, 5:05, December 23, 2017. https://soundcloud.com/balaclub/woesum-sapphire.</ref> Reichwald also serves as the creative director for [[Yung Lean|Yung Lean's]] clothing line Sadboys Gear.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Tesema |first1=Feleg |title=5 of Our Favorite New Collections & Where to Buy Them |url=https://www.highsnobiety.com/p/new-clothing-collections/ |website=[[Highsnobiety]] |publisher=Titel Media |accessdate=19 July 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"need to know\">{{cite web |last1=Dunn |first1=Frankie |title=10 things you need to know about bladee |url=https://i-d.vice.com/en_uk/article/xwmzgz/10-things-you-need-to-know-about-bladee |website=[[i-D]] |publisher=[[Vice Media|Vice]] |accessdate=24 July 2018}}</ref>\n\n== Early life ==\nBenjamin Reichwald was born 9 April 1994 in Stockholm, Sweden<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/BladeeCity/status/718871748674850816|title=Thanks everyone that wish me happy birthday|last=BLAD\u018eE|date=2016-04-09|website=@BladeeCity|language=en|access-date=2019-04-14}}</ref> and was raised mainly in the [[Skanstull]] area.<ref name=BeingBlade>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thefader.com/2019/09/17/bladee-interview-drain-gang-trash-island|title=Being Bladee|last=|first=|date=17 September 2019|website=The Fader|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> It was here where, in 2004, he met fellow Gravity Boys member Zak Arogundade, also known as Ecco2k. The two were classmates and formed a band titled \"Krossad\" when Reichwald was 13, which led to Reichwald's interest in music.<ref name=BeingBlade /> \n\nAfter leaving school, Reichwald began to get into making music whilst working at a daycare centre.<ref name=\"punk mix\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.aqnb.com/2014/07/09/bladee-old-swedish-hardcore-punk-mix/|title=Bladee, old swedish hardcore punk mix|date=2014-07-09|website=atractivoquenobello|language=en-US|access-date=2019-04-14}}</ref>\n\n== Career ==\nReichwald released a few tracks in 2011 under the name Ken Burns<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://genius.com/Bladee-tony-hawk-lyrics|title=Tony Hawk|last=|first=|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ipMrg0edjBM|title=Tony Hawk|last=|first=|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>, but properly began releasing music in 2012. He eventually became friends with fellow Swedish rapper [[Yung Lean]], who was a friend of Reichwald's brother. Reichwald eventually sent a message to Sad Boys member Yung Sherman on SoundCloud, asking to collaborate, which resulted in a working relationship between his own Gravity Boys collective and Lean's Sad Boys Entertainment. Reichwald and Lean then made \"Heal You // Bladerunner\" from Lean's Unknown Death 2002 mixtape, which gave him attention from Lean's fanbase.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thefader.com/2014/07/16/taking-arizona-iced-tea-and-making-it-cry-an-interview-with-yung-lean-and-the-sad-boys|title=\"Taking Arizona Iced Tea and Making It Cry\": An Interview with Yung Lean and the Sad Boys|website=The FADER|language=en|access-date=2019-04-14}}</ref>\n\nReichwald released his debut-mixtape, ''GLUEE'' in 2014 on the YEAR0001 label<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://year0001.com/label/cases/yr0005|title=Bladee - Gluee {{!}} YEAR0001|website=year0001.com|access-date=2019-04-14}}</ref> which was described as the \"summertime anthem for a suburban generation stuck scrolling through Twitter\".<ref name=\"punk mix\"\" /> The mixtape was successful on the audio distribution platform SoundCloud, racking up over 2 million plays.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=0nC0I-z9ONs|title=Always High|last=|first=|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> This mixtape, coupled with several singles going viral and features on Yung Leans debut mixtape [[Unknown Death 2002]] was able to rocket Bladee into underground hip hop fame.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://medium.com/thoughtsofamusicwriter/chronicling-how-sad-boys-and-shield-gang-became-swedens-top-rap-groups-c90925789e6c|title=Chronicling How Sad Boys and Shield Gang Became Sweden's Top Rap Groups|last=Osman|first=Jibril|date=2017-12-20|website=Medium|access-date=2019-04-14}}</ref>\n\nReichwald released his debut album, ''[[Eversince]]'' on May 25th, 2016.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.thefader.com/2016/05/25/bladee-eversince-album-stream||title=Hear Swedish Sing-Rapper Bladee\u2019s Debut Album Eversince|date=May 25, 2016|author=Cooper, Duncan|work=[[The Fader]]|access-date=September 10, 2018|language=en-us}}</ref> The album received mixed reviews from mainstream outlets, but was well-received by underground and experimental critics.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://gaffa.se/recension/107456/kliver-ur-yung-leans-skugga-med-briljant-debut/||title=Kliver ur Yung Leans skugga med briljant debut|date=June 5, 2016|author=Eklund, Jonathan|work=[[Gaffa_(magazine)|Gaffa]]|access-date=September 14, 2018|language=sv}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://noisey.vice.com/en_us/article/6e43we/stream-yung-lean-associate-yung-bladees-chilly-gorgeous-debut-album-eversince|title=Stream Yung Lean Associate Bladee's Chilly, Gorgeous Debut Album 'Eversince'|date=May 25, 2016|author=Jenkins, Craig|work=[[Noisey]]|access-date=September 10, 2018|language=en-us}}</ref>\n\nIn 2017, Reichwald teamed up with production group Working on Dying to release his second mixtape, named after the group.\n\n2018 saw the release of Reichwald's sophomore album, ''[[Red Light (Bladee album)|Red Light]]''.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.thefader.com/2018/05/11/bladee-album-red-light-stream||title=Listen to Bladee\u2019s new album Red Light|date=May 11, 2018|author=Darville, Jordan|work=[[The Fader]]|access-date=September 10, 2018|language=en-us}}</ref>\n\nIn July of 2018, Reichwald and fellow [[Drain Gang]] member [[Ecco2K]] walked Alyx Studio's S/S 2019 menswear show in Paris, on invitation from [[Matthew Williams (fashion designer)|Matthew Williams]].<ref name=Alyx> [https://www.vogue.com/fashion-shows/spring-2019-menswear/alyx \"Alyx S/S 19 Menswear\"], ''[[Vogue (magazine)|Vogue]]'', Retrieved  6 February 2020</ref>\n\nReichwald's third mixtape, ''[[Icedancer]]'', was released December 28, 2018. This album was executively produced by Australian collective Ripsquad featuring production from Whitearmor and PJ Beats.  <ref name=Ice>[https://genius.com/albums/Bladee/Icedancer \"Icedancer\"], [[Genius]]. Retrieved on 6 February 2020.</ref>\n\nIn April of 2020, Reichwald released ''[[EXETER (Bladee album)|EXETER]]''[[EXETER (Bladee album)|,]] a nine song mixtape he recorded whilst in Gotland with [[Gud (music producer)|Gud]]. It is the first Bladee project produced by Gud on the [[YEAR0001]] label. <ref name=EXETER>[https://year0001.com/label/cases/yr0105 \"EXETER\"], [[YEAR0001]]. Retrieved on 8, April 2020.</ref>\n\n== Musical style ==\nReichwald's musical style is characterized by a heavy use of [[autotune]] and a fusion of elements of [[Trap music|trap]], [[alternative R&B]], and [[cloud rap]].<ref name=\"Red Light album review\" /> i-D described his style as \"leaning towards emotional rap with obscure lo-fi production\" though saying, as of 2018, he had \"evolved into some sort of auto-tuned dark angel\".<ref name=\"need to know\" />\n\nIn a 2019 interview, Reichwald acknowledged that he frequently experiments with his music, and does not like to confine what he does to a single genre.<ref name=Jack>Angell, Jack, [https://www.thefader.com/2019/09/17/bladee-interview-drain-gang-trash-island \"Being Bladee\"], ''[[The Fader]]'', Retrieved on 6 February 2020.</ref> In the same interview, he stated that his music is therapeutic for him, and that he often uses it to vent.\n\nIn an interview with Reichwald, Jack Angell, a music writer for [[The Fader]], described Reichwald's sound as \"frostbitten futurism\" and remarked that Reichwald's music evokes \"a wide spectrum of emotion\".<ref name=Jack/>\n\nHe has received widespread attention for his collaborations and live performances with [[Yung Lean]].<ref name=\"debut Decay\" />\n\n==Discography==\n\n===Studio albums===\n\n* ''[[Eversince (Bladee album)|Eversince]]'' (2016)\n* ''[[Red Light (Bladee album)|Red Light]]'' (2018)\n\n===Mixtapes===\n* ''Gluee'' (2014)\n*''Working on Dying'' (2017)\n*''Icedancer'' (2018)\n* ''[[EXETER (Bladee album)|Exeter]]'' (2020)\n\n===Extended plays===\n* ''Rip Bladee'' (2016)\n*''Plastic Surgery'' (2017)<ref>{{Citation|title=Plastic Surgery|date=2017-02-06|url=https://open.spotify.com/album/4hnlDFnmzRYgaVmJYUe89h?si=WUyxx8rsQLO4lcg3enKwnA|language=en|access-date=2018-10-23}}</ref>\n* ''Sunset in Silver City'' (2018)\n* ''Exile'' (2018)\n* ''Vanilla Sky'' (2019)\n\n===Collaborative mixtapes===\n*''GTBSG Compilation'' (2013) <small>(with Thaiboy Digital, Ecco2k, Yung Lean, Whitearmor, Yung Sherman)</small>\n*''AvP'' (2016) <small>(with Thaiboy Digital)</small>\n*''D&G'' (2017) <small>(with Ecco2k, Thaiboy Digital)</small>\n*''Trash Island'' (2019) <small>(with Ecco2k, Thaiboy Digital)</small>\n\n===Singles===\n* \"Oxygen\" (2012)\n* \"Carwash\" (2013)\n* \"I Will Make You Bleed\" (2013) <small>(featuring Thaiboy Digital)</small>\n* \"My Magic Is Strong\" (2013)\n* \"Bleach\" (2013) <small>(featuring Ecco2k)</small>\n* \"Unreal\" (2014)\n* \"Dragonfly\" (2014)\n* \"Into Dust\" (2014)\n* \"Reborn\" (2014)\n* \"Psycho\" (2015) <small>(with Adamn Killa)</small>\n* \"Butterfly\" (2015) <small>(with Thaiboy Digital)</small>\n* \"Who Goes There\" (2016)\n* \"Who's Going To Find Me Tonight\" (2016)\n* \"Destroy Me\" (2017)\n* \"Gotham City\" (2017) <small>(with [[Yung Lean]])</small>\n* \"I Want It All\" (2017) <small>(with Cartier'GOD)</small>\n* \"Plastic Surgery\" (2017)\n* \"Wallet Won't Fold\" (2017)\n* \"Frosty the Snowman\" (2017)\n* \"Decay\" (2018)\n* \"I Chose to Be This Way\" (2018) <small>(with 16yrold)</small>\n* \"Red Velvet\" (2019) <small>(with [[Yung Lean]])</small>\n* \"Trash Star\" (2019)\n* \"All I Want\" (2019) <small>(with Mechatok)</small>\n* \"Apple\" (2019)\n* \"Girls Just Want To Have Fun\" (2020) <small>(with Ecco2k)</small>\n* \"Undergone\" (2020) <small>(with ssaliva)</small>\n\n===Guest appearances===\n* [[Yung Lean]] - \"Nitevision\" (2013)\n* Yung Lean - \"Heal You // Bladerunner\" (2013)\n* Thaiboy Digital - \"Gtblessgo\" (2014)\n* Thaiboy Digital - \"Don't Dance\" (2015)\n* Yung Lean - \"Highway Patrol\" (2016)\n* Yung Lean - \"Hocus Pocus\" (2016)\n* Yung Lean - \"Pearl Fountain\" (2016) <small>(featuring Black Kray)</small>\n* Yung Lean - \"Hennessy & Sailor Moon\" (2016)<ref name=\"HSSWeb\">{{cite web |last1=Renshaw |first1=David |title=Yung Lean Shares Surprise New Song, \"Hennessy & Sailor Moon\" |url=https://www.thefader.com/2016/11/25/yung-lean-hennessy--sailor-moon |website=[[The Fader]] |accessdate=23 September 2018}}</ref>\n* Yung Lean - \"Head 2 Toe\" (2016)\n*D33J - \"10K Froze\" (2018)\n* Yung Lean - \"Red Velvet\" (2019)\n* Varg - \"Perfect Violation\" (2018)\n* Chxpo - \"Do You Love Me\" (2019)\n*Sickboyrari - \"Famous\" (2019) <small>(featuring YSB OG and Yung Lean)</small>\n*Cartier'GOD - \"#LetMeGo\" (2019)\n* Thaiboy Digital - \"Bentley\" (2019)\n* Thaiboy Digital - \"Legendary Member\" (2019)\n*Sickboyrari - \"Blue\" (2019)\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External Links==\n* {{Discogs artist|Bladee}}\n* {{Official website|http://year0001.com/|YEAR0001 Official}}\n\n[[Category:1994 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Swedish rappers]]\n[[Category:Musicians from Stockholm]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox musical artist\n| name             = Bladee\n| background       = solo_singer\n| image            = File:Bladee in Toronto, Canada 2016.jpg\n| caption          = Bladee performing in 2016\n| birth_name       = Benjamin Reichwald\n| alias            = Ken Burns (Sm\u00f6g Boys)\n| birth_date       = {{birth date and age|1994|4|9|df=y}}\n| birth_place      = [[Stockholm, Sweden]]\n| genre            = [[cloud rap]], [[emo rap]], [[experimental pop]]\n| occupation       = [[Rapper]], [[Singing|singer]], [[Fashion designer]], [[Graphic designer]]\n| instrument       = [[Vocals]], [[Digital Audio Workstation]], [[pitch-correction software]]\n| years_active     = 2008; 2011; 2012\u2013present\n| label            = {{hlist|[[YEAR0001]]|[[AWAL]]}}\n| associated_acts  = {{hlist|[[Yung Lean]]|[[Thaiboy Digital]]|[[ECCO2K]]|Whitearmor|Yung Sherman|Gud|Adamn Killa|Cartier'GOD|Black Kray}}\n}}\n'''Benjamin Thage Dag Reichwald'''<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://genius.com/artists/Bladee|title=Bladee|last=|first=|date=|website=Genius|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Borelli-Persson |first1=Laird |title=Is There Anything He Can't Do? Meet Stockholm's Stylish Multi-Hyphenate Zak Arogundade |url=https://www.vogue.com/article/musicians-zak-arogundade |website=[[Vogue (magazine)|Vogue]] |publisher=Cond\u00e9 Nast |accessdate=7 July 2018}}</ref> (born 9 April 1994<ref>{{cite tweet |user=BladeeCity |number=718871748674850816 |date=9 Apr 2016 |title=Thanks everyone that wished me happy birthday}}</ref>), known professionally as '''Bladee''' (pronounced either \"blade\" or \"blade-e\"),<ref>\"Nardwuar vs. Yung Lean\", Youtube video, 12:36, posted by \"[[Nardwuar the Human Serviette|NardwuarServiette]]\", July 23, 2014, https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=723ywF5faV4.</ref> is a Swedish rapper, singer, songwriter, record-producer, fashion designer and member of the musical group [[Drain Gang]].<ref name=Darville2018>{{cite web |last1=Darville |first1=Jordan |title=Listen to Bladee's new album Red Light |url=https://www.thefader.com/2018/05/11/bladee-album-red-light-stream |website=[[The Fader]] |publisher=Andy Cohn |accessdate=7 July 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"Red Light album review\">\"Bladee - Red Light ALBUM REVIEW\", Youtube video, 5:21, posted by \"[[Anthony Fantano|theneedledrop]]\", June 21, 2018, https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=FJwmTnjDkrI.</ref><ref name=\"debut Decay\">{{cite web |last1=Wang |first1=Steffanee |title=Bladee debuts \"Decay,\" our first taste of new album Red Light |url=https://www.thefader.com/2018/05/02/bladee-decay-video-red-light-album |website=[[The Fader]] |publisher=Andy Cohn |accessdate=19 July 2018}}</ref> \n\nHe released his debut album ''[[Eversince (Bladee album)|Eversince]]'' in 2016, and his second album ''[[Red Light (Bladee album)|Red Light]]'' in 2018\u2014both through Stockholm record label [[YEAR0001]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=Jenkins |first1=Craig |title=Stream Yung Lean Associate Bladee's Chilly, Gorgeous Debut Album 'Eversince' |url=https://noisey.vice.com/en_us/article/6e43we/stream-yung-lean-associate-yung-bladees-chilly-gorgeous-debut-album-eversince |website=[[Noisey]] |publisher=[[Vice Media]] |accessdate=7 July 2018}}</ref><ref name=Darville2018 /><ref>YEAR0001. Accessed July 19, 2018. http://www.year0001.com/.</ref> In addition to his music, Reichwald creates visual art, which frequently appears as cover art for his releases.<ref>Sami Baha. \"Bladee - Cover Up (Prod. Sami Baha)\". Soundcloud audio, 2:38, June 27, 2018. https://soundcloud.com/samibaha/bladee-cover-up-prod-sami-baha.</ref><ref>Bala Club. \"Woesum - Sapphire\". Soundcloud audio, 5:05, December 23, 2017. https://soundcloud.com/balaclub/woesum-sapphire.</ref> Reichwald also serves as the creative director for [[Yung Lean|Yung Lean's]] clothing line Sadboys Gear.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Tesema |first1=Feleg |title=5 of Our Favorite New Collections & Where to Buy Them |url=https://www.highsnobiety.com/p/new-clothing-collections/ |website=[[Highsnobiety]] |publisher=Titel Media |accessdate=19 July 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"need to know\">{{cite web |last1=Dunn |first1=Frankie |title=10 things you need to know about bladee |url=https://i-d.vice.com/en_uk/article/xwmzgz/10-things-you-need-to-know-about-bladee |website=[[i-D]] |publisher=[[Vice Media|Vice]] |accessdate=24 July 2018}}</ref>\n\n== Early life ==\nBenjamin Reichwald was born 9 April 1994 in Stockholm, Sweden<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/BladeeCity/status/718871748674850816|title=Thanks everyone that wish me happy birthday|last=BLAD\u018eE|date=2016-04-09|website=@BladeeCity|language=en|access-date=2019-04-14}}</ref> and was raised mainly in the [[Skanstull]] area.<ref name=BeingBlade>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thefader.com/2019/09/17/bladee-interview-drain-gang-trash-island|title=Being Bladee|last=|first=|date=17 September 2019|website=The Fader|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> It was here where, in 2004, he met fellow Gravity Boys member Zak Arogundade, also known as Ecco2k. The two were classmates and formed a band titled \"Krossad\" when Reichwald was 13, which led to Reichwald's interest in music.<ref name=BeingBlade /> \n\nAfter leaving school, Reichwald began to get into making music whilst working at a daycare centre.<ref name=\"punk mix\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.aqnb.com/2014/07/09/bladee-old-swedish-hardcore-punk-mix/|title=Bladee, old swedish hardcore punk mix|date=2014-07-09|website=atractivoquenobello|language=en-US|access-date=2019-04-14}}</ref>\n\n== Career ==\nReichwald released a few tracks in 2011 under the name Ken Burns<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://genius.com/Bladee-tony-hawk-lyrics|title=Tony Hawk|last=|first=|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ipMrg0edjBM|title=Tony Hawk|last=|first=|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>, but properly began releasing music in 2012. He eventually became friends with fellow Swedish rapper [[Yung Lean]], who was a friend of Reichwald's brother. Reichwald eventually sent a message to Sad Boys member Yung Sherman on SoundCloud, asking to collaborate, which resulted in a working relationship between his own Gravity Boys collective and Lean's Sad Boys Entertainment. Reichwald and Lean then made \"Heal You // Bladerunner\" from Lean's Unknown Death 2002 mixtape, which gave him attention from Lean's fanbase.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thefader.com/2014/07/16/taking-arizona-iced-tea-and-making-it-cry-an-interview-with-yung-lean-and-the-sad-boys|title=\"Taking Arizona Iced Tea and Making It Cry\": An Interview with Yung Lean and the Sad Boys|website=The FADER|language=en|access-date=2019-04-14}}</ref>\n\nReichwald released his debut-mixtape, ''GLUEE'' in 2014 on the YEAR0001 label<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://year0001.com/label/cases/yr0005|title=Bladee - Gluee {{!}} YEAR0001|website=year0001.com|access-date=2019-04-14}}</ref> which was described as the \"summertime anthem for a suburban generation stuck scrolling through Twitter\".<ref name=\"punk mix\"\" /> The mixtape was successful on the audio distribution platform SoundCloud, racking up over 2 million plays.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=0nC0I-z9ONs|title=Always High|last=|first=|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> This mixtape, coupled with several singles going viral and features on Yung Leans debut mixtape [[Unknown Death 2002]] was able to rocket Bladee into underground hip hop fame.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://medium.com/thoughtsofamusicwriter/chronicling-how-sad-boys-and-shield-gang-became-swedens-top-rap-groups-c90925789e6c|title=Chronicling How Sad Boys and Shield Gang Became Sweden's Top Rap Groups|last=Osman|first=Jibril|date=2017-12-20|website=Medium|access-date=2019-04-14}}</ref>\n\nReichwald released his debut album, ''[[Eversince]]'' on May 25th, 2016.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.thefader.com/2016/05/25/bladee-eversince-album-stream||title=Hear Swedish Sing-Rapper Bladee\u2019s Debut Album Eversince|date=May 25, 2016|author=Cooper, Duncan|work=[[The Fader]]|access-date=September 10, 2018|language=en-us}}</ref> The album received mixed reviews from mainstream outlets, but was well-received by underground and experimental critics.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://gaffa.se/recension/107456/kliver-ur-yung-leans-skugga-med-briljant-debut/||title=Kliver ur Yung Leans skugga med briljant debut|date=June 5, 2016|author=Eklund, Jonathan|work=[[Gaffa_(magazine)|Gaffa]]|access-date=September 14, 2018|language=sv}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://noisey.vice.com/en_us/article/6e43we/stream-yung-lean-associate-yung-bladees-chilly-gorgeous-debut-album-eversince|title=Stream Yung Lean Associate Bladee's Chilly, Gorgeous Debut Album 'Eversince'|date=May 25, 2016|author=Jenkins, Craig|work=[[Noisey]]|access-date=September 10, 2018|language=en-us}}</ref>\n\nIn 2017, Reichwald teamed up with production group Working on Dying to release his second mixtape, named after the group.\n\n2018 saw the release of Reichwald's sophomore album, ''[[Red Light (Bladee album)|Red Light]]''.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.thefader.com/2018/05/11/bladee-album-red-light-stream||title=Listen to Bladee\u2019s new album Red Light|date=May 11, 2018|author=Darville, Jordan|work=[[The Fader]]|access-date=September 10, 2018|language=en-us}}</ref>\n\nIn July of 2018, Reichwald and fellow [[Drain Gang]] member [[Ecco2K]] walked Alyx Studio's S/S 2019 menswear show in Paris, on invitation from [[Matthew Williams (fashion designer)|Matthew Williams]].<ref name=Alyx> [https://www.vogue.com/fashion-shows/spring-2019-menswear/alyx \"Alyx S/S 19 Menswear\"], ''[[Vogue (magazine)|Vogue]]'', Retrieved  6 February 2020</ref>\n\nReichwald's third mixtape, ''[[Icedancer]]'', was released December 28, 2018. This album was executively produced by Australian collective Ripsquad featuring production from Whitearmor and PJ Beats.  <ref name=Ice>[https://genius.com/albums/Bladee/Icedancer \"Icedancer\"], [[Genius]]. Retrieved on 6 February 2020.</ref>\n\nIn April of 2020, Reichwald released ''[[EXETER (Bladee album)|EXETER]]''[[EXETER (Bladee album)|,]] a nine song mixtape he recorded whilst in Gotland with Yung Gud. It is the first Bladee project produced by [[Yung Gud]] on the [[YEAR0001]] label. <ref name=EXETER>[https://year0001.com/label/cases/yr0105 \"EXETER\"], [[YEAR0001]]. Retrieved on 8, April 2020.</ref>\n\n== Musical style ==\nReichwald's musical style is characterized by a heavy use of [[autotune]] and a fusion of elements of [[Trap music|trap]], [[alternative R&B]], and [[cloud rap]].<ref name=\"Red Light album review\" /> i-D described his style as \"leaning towards emotional rap with obscure lo-fi production\" though saying, as of 2018, he had \"evolved into some sort of auto-tuned dark angel\".<ref name=\"need to know\" />\n\nIn a 2019 interview, Reichwald acknowledged that he frequently experiments with his music, and does not like to confine what he does to a single genre.<ref name=Jack>Angell, Jack, [https://www.thefader.com/2019/09/17/bladee-interview-drain-gang-trash-island \"Being Bladee\"], ''[[The Fader]]'', Retrieved on 6 February 2020.</ref> In the same interview, he stated that his music is therapeutic for him, and that he often uses it to vent.\n\nIn an interview with Reichwald, Jack Angell, a music writer for [[The Fader]], described Reichwald's sound as \"frostbitten futurism\" and remarked that Reichwald's music evokes \"a wide spectrum of emotion\".<ref name=Jack/>\n\nHe has received widespread attention for his collaborations and live performances with [[Yung Lean]].<ref name=\"debut Decay\" />\n\n==Discography==\n\n===Studio albums===\n\n* ''[[Eversince (Bladee album)|Eversince]]'' (2016)\n* ''[[Red Light (Bladee album)|Red Light]]'' (2018)\n\n===Mixtapes===\n* ''Gluee'' (2014)\n*''Working on Dying'' (2017)\n*''Icedancer'' (2018)\n* ''[[EXETER (Bladee album)|Exeter]]'' (2020)\n\n===Extended plays===\n* ''Rip Bladee'' (2016)\n*''Plastic Surgery'' (2017)<ref>{{Citation|title=Plastic Surgery|date=2017-02-06|url=https://open.spotify.com/album/4hnlDFnmzRYgaVmJYUe89h?si=WUyxx8rsQLO4lcg3enKwnA|language=en|access-date=2018-10-23}}</ref>\n* ''Sunset in Silver City'' (2018)\n* ''Exile'' (2018)\n* ''Vanilla Sky'' (2019)\n\n===Collaborative mixtapes===\n*''GTBSG Compilation'' (2013) <small>(with Thaiboy Digital, Ecco2k, Yung Lean, Whitearmor, Yung Sherman)</small>\n*''AvP'' (2016) <small>(with Thaiboy Digital)</small>\n*''D&G'' (2017) <small>(with Ecco2k, Thaiboy Digital)</small>\n*''Trash Island'' (2019) <small>(with Ecco2k, Thaiboy Digital)</small>\n\n===Singles===\n* \"Oxygen\" (2012)\n* \"Carwash\" (2013)\n* \"I WILL MAKE YOU BLEED\" (2013) <small>(featuring Thaiboy Digital)</small>\n* \"my magic is strong\" (2013)\n* \"Bleach\" (2013) <small>(featuring Ecco2k)</small>\n* \"Unreal\" (2014)\n* \"Dragonfly\" (2014)\n* \"Into Dust\" (2014)\n* \"Reborn\" (2014)\n* \"Psycho\" (2015) <small>(with Adamn Killa)</small>\n* \"Butterfly\" (2015) <small>(with Thaiboy Digital)</small>\n* \"Who Goes There\" (2016)\n* \"Who's Going To Find Me Tonight\" (2016)\n* \"Destroy Me\" (2017)\n* \"Gotham City\" (2017) <small>(with [[Yung Lean]])</small>\n* \"I Want It All\" (2017) <small>(with Cartier'GOD)</small>\n* \"Plastic Surgery\" (2017)\n* \"Wallet Won't Fold\" (2017)\n* \"Frosty the Snowman\" (2017)\n* \"Decay\" (2018)\n* \"I Chose to Be This Way\" (2018) <small>(with 16yrold)</small>\n* \"Red Velvet\" (2019) <small>(with [[Yung Lean]])</small>\n* \"Trash Star\" (2019)\n* \"All I Want\" (2019) <small>(with Mechatok)</small>\n* \"Apple\" (2019)\n* \"Girls just want to have fun\" (2020) <small>(with Ecco2k)</small>\n* \"Undergone\" (2020) <small>(with ssaliva)</small>\n\n===Guest appearances===\n* [[Yung Lean]] - \"Nitevision\" (2013)\n* Yung Lean - \"Heal You // Bladerunner\" (2013)\n* Thaiboy Digital - \"Gtblessgo\" (2014)\n* Thaiboy Digital - \"Don't Dance\" (2015)\n* Yung Lean - \"Highway Patrol\" (2016)\n* Yung Lean - \"Hocus Pocus\" (2016)\n* Yung Lean - \"Pearl Fountain\" (2016) <small>(featuring Black Kray)</small>\n* Yung Lean - \"Hennessy & Sailor Moon\" (2016)<ref name=\"HSSWeb\">{{cite web |last1=Renshaw |first1=David |title=Yung Lean Shares Surprise New Song, \"Hennessy & Sailor Moon\" |url=https://www.thefader.com/2016/11/25/yung-lean-hennessy--sailor-moon |website=[[The Fader]] |accessdate=23 September 2018}}</ref>\n* Yung Lean - \"Head 2 Toe\" (2016)\n*D33J - \"10K Froze\" (2018)\n* Yung Lean - \"Red Velvet\" (2019)\n* Varg - \"Perfect Violation\" (2018)\n* Chxpo - \"Do You Love Me\" (2019)\n*Sickboyrari - \"Famous\" (2019) <small>(featuring YSB OG and Yung Lean)</small>\n*Cartier'GOD - \"#LetMeGo\" (2019)\n* Thaiboy Digital - \"Bentley\" (2019)\n* Thaiboy Digital - \"Legendary Member\" (2019)\n*Sickboyrari - \"Blue\" (2019)\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External Links==\n* {{Discogs artist|Bladee}}\n* {{Official website|http://year0001.com/|YEAR0001 Official}}\n\n[[Category:1994 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Swedish rappers]]\n[[Category:Musicians from Stockholm]]\n", "name_user": "Cantabile22", "label": "safe", "comment": "Changed capitalization for the singles and corrected the stage name for Gud.", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bladee"}
{"title_page": "2019\u201320 EFL Cup", "text_new": "{{Infobox football tournament season\n| title           = EFL Cup\n| year            = 2019\u201320\n| other_titles    = Carabao Cup, League Cup\n| caption         = \n| country         = England<br />Wales\n| dates           = 6 August 2019 \u2013 1 March 2020\n| num_teams       = 91\n| champions       = Manchester City\n| defending_champions = [[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]]\n| count           = 7\n| runner-up       = [[Aston Villa F.C.|Aston Villa]]\n| matches         = 92\n| goals           = 227\n| attendance      = 960406\n| top goal scorer = [[Liam Boyce]] (5 goals)\n| player          = \n| prevseason      = [[2018\u201319 EFL Cup|2018\u201319]]\n| nextseason      = ''2020\u201321''\n}}\nThe '''2019\u201320 EFL Cup''' was the 60th season of the [[EFL Cup]]. Also known as the '''Carabao Cup''' for sponsorship reasons, the competition was open to all clubs participating in the [[Premier League]] and the [[English Football League]].\n\n[[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]] were the two-time defending champions, having retained the trophy in [[2019 EFL Cup Final|2019]], and won their third consecutive title, defeating [[Aston Villa F.C.|Aston Villa]] in the [[2020 EFL Cup Final|final]] at [[Wembley Stadium]] in London on 1 March 2020.<ref name=\"KD\">{{cite web |url=https://www.efl.com/news/2019/april/key-dates-announced-ahead-of-201920-season/|title=Key dates announced ahead of 2019/20 season|publisher=English Football League|date=17 April 2019 |accessdate=31 May 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Access==\nAll 92 clubs in the Premier League and English Football League entered the season's EFL Cup. Access was distributed across the top 4 leagues of the [[English football league system]]. For the first two rounds, the draw was regionalised into northern and southern clubs.\n\nIn the first round, 22 of 24 [[2019\u201320 EFL Championship|Championship]] clubs and all [[2019\u201320 EFL League One|League One]], and [[2019\u201320 EFL League Two|League Two]] clubs entered. Due to their financial crisis, [[Bury F.C.|Bury]] were later withdrawn from the competition and ultimately expelled from the [[English Football League|EFL]].<ref name=\"Bury\"/> [[Sheffield Wednesday F.C.|Sheffield Wednesday]], who were Bury's first round opponents, advanced to the second round automatically as a result.\n\nThe following round, the two remaining Championship clubs [[Cardiff City F.C.|Cardiff City]] and [[Fulham F.C.|Fulham]] (who finished 18th and 19th respectively in the [[2018\u201319 Premier League]] season), and the [[2019\u201320 Premier League|Premier League]] clubs not involved in either the [[2019\u201320 UEFA Champions League|Champions League]] or [[2019\u201320 UEFA Europa League|Europa League]] entered.\n\n[[Arsenal F.C.|Arsenal]], [[Chelsea F.C.|Chelsea]], [[Liverpool F.C.|Liverpool]], [[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]], [[Manchester United F.C.|Manchester United]], [[Tottenham Hotspur F.C.|Tottenham Hotspur]], and [[Wolverhampton Wanderers F.C.|Wolverhampton Wanderers]] all received byes to the third round owing to their participation in European competitions.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/47529462 |title=Premier League, EFL, Scottish football: Ups, downs & European qualification |publisher=BBC Sport |date=27 May 2019 |accessdate=31 May 2019}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!\n!Clubs entering in this round\n!Clubs advancing from previous round\n!Number of games\n|-\n!First round<br />(70 clubs)\n|\n*24 clubs from EFL League Two\n*24 clubs from EFL League One\n*22 clubs from EFL Championship\n|\n*N/A\n|35\n|-\n!Second round<br />(50 clubs)\n|\n*2 clubs from EFL Championship\n*13 Premier League clubs (not involved in European competition)\n|\n*35 winners from first round\n|25\n|-\n!Third round<br />(32 clubs)\n|\n*7 Premier League clubs (involved in European competition)\n|\n*25 winners from second round\n|16\n|-\n!Fourth round<br />(16 clubs)\n|\n*No clubs enter the fourth round\n|\n*16 winners from third round\n|8\n|-\n!Quarter-finals<br />(8 clubs)\n|\n*No clubs enter the quarter-finals\n|\n*8 winners from fourth round\n|4\n|-\n!Semi-finals<br />(4 clubs)\n|\n*No clubs enter the semi-finals\n|\n*4 winners from fifth round\n|4 (2 legs for each semi-final)\n|-\n!Final<br />(2 clubs)\n|\n*No clubs enter the final\n|\n*2 winners from semi-finals\n|1\n|}\n\n== First round ==\nA total of 70 clubs played in the first round: 24 from [[EFL League Two|League Two]] (tier 4), 24 from [[EFL League One|League One]] (tier 3), and 22 from the [[EFL Championship|Championship]] (tier 2). The draw for this round was split on a geographical basis into 'northern' and 'southern' sections. Teams were drawn against a team from the same section. The draw was made by [[John Barnes (footballer)|John Barnes]] and [[Ray Parlour]] on 20 June 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.goal.com/en/news/carabao-cup-2019-20-fixtures-teams-draw-dates-all-you-need/s3lrhq8sfkcc1rj62swcmv0mx|title=Carabao Cup 2019\u201320: Fixtures, teams, draw dates & all you need to know|last=|first=|date=20 June 2019|website=Goal.com|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n{{Football box collapsible|id=Portsmouth v Birmingham City|date=6 August 2019|time=19:45 [[British Summer Time|BST]]|round=|score=3\u20130|report=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/49160095|team1=[[Portsmouth F.C.|Portsmouth]] (3)|goals1=[[Ellis Harrison|Harrison]]\n {{goal|30||54}}<br />[[Ben Close|Close]] {{goal|39}}|team2='''[[Birmingham City F.C.|Birmingham City]] (2)'''|goals2=|stadium=[[Fratton Park]]|location=[[Portsmouth]]|attendance=9,913|referee=Neil Hair}}\n{{Football box collapsible|id=Accrington Stanley v Sunderland|date=13 August 2019|time=19:45 [[British Summer Time|BST]]|round=|score=1\u20133|report=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/49245362|team1='''[[Accrington Stanley F.C.|Accrington Stanley]] (3)'''|goals1=  [[Colby Bishop|Bishop]]{{goal|61|pen}}|team2=[[Sunderland 